text: Suzaku named after the mythological "vermilion bird of the south". is the name of the a Japanese artificial satellite which was put into orbit in 2005. The launch was a project of the Institute of Space and Astronautical Science of the University of Tokyo. The satellite was launched on July 10, 2005.JAXA, "Catalogue of ISAS Missions" ; retrieved 2012-4-2. == References == == Other websites == * Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA), Suzaku (ASTRO-EII) mission profile Category:Japanese satellites Category:Spacecrafts launched in 2000s
